  "body": "### Description\n\nCurrently the `quarkus-test-security-jwt` extension only supports configuring `String` claims, so it becomes a little difficult to configure more complex claims.\r\nFor example, my code needs to read the `exp`, `iat`, `realm_access` claims, which are not `String` claims.\r\nIt isn't very hard to adapt my code to parse these claims as `String` if necessary, but it is a bit bothersome as this code should not be necessary.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n\r\n```\r\n@Test\r\n@TestSecurity(user = \"testUser\", roles = {\"active_user\"})\r\n@JwtSecurity(\r\n\t\tclaims = {\r\n\t\t\t@Claim(key = \"language\", value = \"pt\"),\r\n\t\t\t@Claim(key = \"country\", value = \"PT\"),\r\n\t\t\t@Claim(key = \"exp\", value = \"9999999999\"),\r\n\t\t\t@Claim(key = \"iat\", value = \"0\"),\r\n\t\t\t@Claim(key = \"azp\", value = \"test\"),\r\n\t\t\t@Claim(key = \"sub\", value = \"testUser\"),\r\n\t\t\t@Claim(key = \"realm_access\", value = \"{\\\"roles\\\":[\\\"active_user\\\"]}\")\r\n\t\t}\r\n)\r\nvoid activateCampaign_ValidPayload() {\r\n\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nCan you add support for this extension to, at least, map `JSON` and `Array` type claims properly?\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
